
meta-rno-g
============

This layer contains customizations on top of meta-ampliphy/meta-phytec for the RNO-G experiment when using the AM62X SOM

The top-level image is called rno-g-station

To use, you probably want to set up the environment as specified on the on the phytec website, set machine to rno-g-revn, distro to ampliphy, then add this layer.

Then bitbake rno-g-station



Cosmin Deaconu <cozzyd@kicp.uchicago.edu>
